    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="261" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Leech</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Jackson</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. John,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 10, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed by the Secretary of State that steamer Chesapeake, of
                                Portland and New York line, has been taken possession of by supposed
                                insurgents on board, off Cape Cod, the second engineer killed, and
                                the captain landed at St. John, New Brunswick. We are instructed to
                                use our best efforts to cause the arrest of the criminals, and the
                                detention of the steamer. Am requested to inform you she has not
                                been seen here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C. O. LEACH, <hi rend="italic">United States
                                    Consul.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
